address: Howon Art Hall 30 Seongan-ro, Seongnae 3-dong Gangdong-gu, Seoul, Korea
234 Artvalley-ro, Sinbuk-myeon, Pocheon-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea
description: Since 2005, Pocheon City has rebuilt the abandoned quarry in Giji-ri, Sinbuk-myeon since 2003, into a multi-cultural art space that heals and restores the environment with culture and art. In October 2009, it was finally built as Pocheon Art Valley. Taking full advantage of the original quarry terrain, a sculpture park, exhibition hall, and amphitheater have been constructed. The quarry valley has also been used to build an observatory, a stone culture exhibition hall, and a monorail. There are many things to see. And in the Art Valley, you can also experience culture, art, and education, give play to unlimited imagination, and integrate nature with people.
